anish and others said it was portuguese at the time they were growing both lemons and oranges and  was a milestone for the company when it planted  orange trees its first nonlemon product by  the company had nearly  trees consisting of  lemon trees  grapefruit trees and  orange trees this year blanchard also retired and appointed charles m teague as his successor the limoneira plantation also had its own fire department which still exists today and is one of the oldest continuously operating fire departments in ventura county in  limoneira achieved its first net profit and paid its first dividend to stockholders the following year in  limoneira purchased the  acre olivelands tract acquiring  of agriculture for walnuts olives beans corn and hay and because it converted  to livestock grazing the company also purchased the santa paula and horse and feed company the next year in january  the newspaper ventura free press ran a story for limoneira called greatest lemon ranch in the world saying a further increase in the size of the largest lemon plantation in the worldwill be the result of planting this season at the limoneira ranch there are now bearing lemon trees on the property and this year trees will be on  acres more the crop last year was the largest since the planting has begunbigness is not the chief end kept in view the management of the ranch the growth of the enterprise in fact has come from never flagging efforts to maintain and improve the quality of the product in addition to lemons the ranch has  acres of walnuts by  the companys growth was evident and the santa paula chronicle said the lemoneira sic company has demonstrated the wisdom of ample frost protection the company will ship more than  cars of lemons this year approximately onethird of the entire amount to the be shipped from this state by  the company was battling sunkist as both of them had nationally recognized products and limoneira refused to exclusively brand their oranges as sunkist but later reluctantly agreed by the s the company’s acreage under cultivation had quadrupled in less than  years and numerous building and expansion projects were underway it was the solid base created in the previous  years that pulled the company through the depression and the challenges of the s in  with teague as the manager he built the company into the states largest citrus holding and the worlds largest acreage the company also joined the southern california fruit exchange before pulling out a few years later and joining again in  the company also once set the record for deepest oil well in ventura county before abandoning the well in  the well like many others were in search of oil but oil was never found on limoneira properties despite several companies participating in drilling including superior oil company richfield oil corporation humble oil unocal corporation and standard oil throughout its history it has employed foreign labor includind japanese and mexicans in  after the immigration act of  which barred japanese immigration it particularly focused on mexican labor since the s limoneira has also been a leading lemon supplier to japan and also distributes to korea china philippines and thailand in  limoneira partnered with samuel edwards associates to become limoneira associates until limoneira become one company again in  in  limoneira made a crossequity agreement with calavo growers where limoneira got a  stake of calavo while calavo got a  stake in limoneira in  limoneira acquired associated citrus packers inc of yuma arizona for  million in  it acquired martin ranching company for  million overviewedit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed january  learn how and when to remove this template message limoneira company operates as an agribusiness and real estate development company and is one of the largest growers and marketers of lemons in the us and the largest grower of avocados in the us the company has  acres of agriculture and real estate property and significant water rights operations are in california arizona and chile operates in agribusiness rental operations and real estate development agribusinessedit the agribusiness segment grows lemons avocados oranges and various specialty citrus fruits and other crops such as satsuma mandarin oranges moro blood oranges cara cara oranges minneola tangelos star ruby grapefruit pummelos pistachios and olives as well as pack and sell lemons grown by others this segment sells and markets lemons directly to food service wholesale and retail customers it has  acres of lemons approximately  acres of avocados approximately  acres of oranges and approximately  acres of specialty citrus and other crops in ventura and tulare counties california and yuma county in arizona the company also has a  interest in rosales sa a citrus packing marketing and sales operation in la serena chile limoneira owns two packing facilitiesone in santa paula california and the other in yuma arizona rental operationsedit the rental operations segment rents residential and commercial properties such as office buildings and a multiuse facility consisting of a retail convenience store gas station car wash and quickserve restaurant the company also owns and rents  work force housing units and leases approximately  acres of land to third party agricultural tenants real estate developmentedit the company is one of the largest land owners in ventura county california the real estate development segment develops land parcels multifamily housing and singlefamily homes the company is developing east area i and ii in santa paula a acre master planned community with  residential units sf of commercial space and sf of light industrial spacelimoneira also owns windfall farms in creston california san luis obispo county a acre subdividable  acre vineyard estate parcels which has been planted with  acres of cabernet sauvignon wine grapes the company also owns three commercial parcels in santa maria california with rights to develop  residential units sustainabilityedit limoneira employs sustainable practices in virtually each aspect of its daytoday business and has made strategic investments in solar water soil and ipm integrated pest management solaredit in  limoneira completed two stateoftheart solar projects the first at company headquarters in santa paula ca is a acre photovoltaic orchard that generates a full megawatt of electricity representing onethird of the company’s total use solar energy powers limoneira’s lemonpacking house and storage facility in the tulare county town of ducor about  miles north of santa paula limoneira installed four smaller solar arrays that together generate another full megawatt of electricity to power horsepower motors that pump deep well water into reservoirs for the irrigation of  agricultural acres it is estimated that over their expected year lifespan limoneira’s solar generation of  million kilowatt hours will save at least  tons of greenhouse gases that would have otherwise been emitted by an ordinary oil or coalfiring power plant water rightsedit through limoneira’s land position historic water use sustainable land use practices and by making investments in infrastructure the company has developed longterm firm and reliable rights to water sufficient to meet any of the company’s land use objectives organic recyclingedit in  limoneira company partnered with agromin to create an innovative organic recycling program agromin is a manufacturer of premium soil products and the green waste recycler for more than  communities cities in los angeles orange santa barbara and ventura counties limoneira and agromin developed a acre facility on limoneira land to receive green materials lawn clipping leaves bark plant materials from throughout ventura county the material is converted into mulch that is spread in limoneira orchards to curb erosion improve water efficiency reduce weeds and moderate soil temperatures integrated pest managementedit limoneira was one of the founders of associates insectary this growerowned cooperative was formed in  and provides pest control services to commercial citrus and avocado farmers beneficial insects are bred to control destructive agricultural pests limoneira maintains a complete integrated pest management system to bring our sustainablygrown products to market achievementsedit received recognition from the white house received ipm innovator award at california legislature assembly resolution ipm innovator award by california environmental protection agency referencesedit  people limoneira co lmno reuters retrieved  november    limoneira co stock quote  summary data nasdaq retrieved  november    adam newman andrew a lemon grower emphasizes uses for citrus outside the kitchen the new york times retrieved  november    limoneira company yahoo finance retrieved  november    press release limoneira teams up with new york partners to unleash the power of lemons reuters   forouzandeh hossein insider selling john w blanchard sells  shares of limoneira stock lmnr mid east time archived from the original on    a b california legislature assembly resolution pdf california state assembly archived from the original pdf on  december  retrieved  november    labor in the california citrus industry  university of california berkeley  western fruit grower   californias citrus city the spokesmanreview july   retrieved july     a b nash bill  oil orchards and flames the history of firefighting in santa paula xlibris pp – isbn  retrieved july     california historical society quarterly volume    mcbane margo winter  whitening a california citrus company town racial segregation practices at the limoneira company and santa paula – raceethnicity multidisciplinary global contexts   reworking race and labor – doiracethmulglocon   home  about us  history limoneiracom archived fr