management  achievements  references  external links historyedit limoneiras lemon exhibit right was featured at the alaska–yukon–pacific exposition in  limoneira was founded in  at union oil company building in santa paula california by nathan blanchard sr one of the founders of santa paula and wallace hardison and started with  acres of land which over time would increase as the company grew there are several stories behind the name limoneira with some saying it came from spanish and others said it was portuguese at the time they were growing both lemons and oranges and  was a milestone for the company when it planted  orange trees its first nonlemon product by  the company had nearly  trees consisting of  lemon trees  grapefruit trees and  orange trees this year blanchard also retired and appointed charles m teague as his successor the limoneira plantation also had its own fire department which still exists today and is one of the oldest continuously operating fire departments in ventura county in  limoneira achieved its first net profit and paid its first dividend to stockholders the following year in  limoneira purchased the  acre olivelands tract acquiring  of agriculture for walnuts olives beans corn and hay and because it converted  to livestock grazing the company also purchased the santa paula and horse and feed company the next year in january  the newspaper ventura free press ran a story for limoneira called greatest lemon ranch in the world saying a further increase in the size of the largest lemon plantation in the worldwill be the result of planting this season at the limoneira ranch there are now bearing lemon trees on the property and this year trees will be on  acres more the crop last year was the largest since the planting has begunbigness is not the chief end kept in view the management of the ranch the growth of the enterprise in fact has come from never flagging efforts to maintain and improve the quality of the product in addition to lemons th