ental operations and real estate development total assets  website limoneiracom limoneira is a public limited agribusiness and real estate development company based in california united states the companys operations mainly consist of production sales and marketing of citrus and avocados  they have three business segments which are agribusiness rental operations and real estate development the company received the ipm innovator award at california legislature assembly resolution it has repeatedly been called one of the largest lemon producers in the state and world including one of the oldest citrus growing organizations of the west coast the oldest ongoing citrus operation in california contents  history  overview  agribusiness  rental operations  real estate development  sustainability  solar  water rights  organic recycling  integrated pest management  achievements  references  external links historyedit limoneiras lemon exhibit right was featured at the alaska–yukon–pacific exposition in  limoneira was founded in  at union oil company building in santa paula california by nathan blanchard sr one of the founders of santa paula and wallace hardison and started with  acres of land which over time would increase as the company grew there are several stories behind the name limoneira with some saying it came from spanish and others said it was portuguese at the time they were growing both lemons and oranges and  was a milestone for the company when it planted  orange trees its first nonlemon product by  the company had nearly  trees consisting of  lemon trees  grapefruit trees and  orange trees this year blanchard also retired and appointed charles m teague as his successor the limoneira plantation also had its own fire department which still exists today and is one of the oldest continuously operating fire departments in ventura county in  limoneira achieved its first net profit and paid its first dividend to stockholders the following year in  limoneira purchased the  acre olivelands tract acquiring  of agriculture for walnuts olives beans corn and hay and because it converted  to livestock grazing the company also purchased the santa paula and horse and feed company the next year in january  the newspaper ventura free press ran a story for limoneira called greatest lemon ranch in the world saying a further increase in the size of the largest lemon plantation in the worldwill be the result of planting this season at the limoneira ranch there are now bearing lemon trees on the property and this year trees will be on  acres more the crop last year was the largest since the planting has begunbigness is not the chief end kept in view the management of the ranch the growth of the enterprise in fact has come from never flagging efforts to maintain and improve the quality of the product in addition to lemons the ranch has  acres of walnuts by  the companys growth was evident and the santa paula chronicle said the lemoneira sic company has demonstrated the wisdom of ample frost protection the company will ship more than  cars of lemons this year approximately onethird of the entire amount to the be shipped from this state by  the company was battling sunkist as both of them had nationally recognized products and limoneira refused to exclusively brand their oranges as sunkist but later reluctantly agreed by the s the company’s acreage under cultivation had quadrupled in less than  years and numerous building and expansion projects were underway it was the solid base created in the previous  years that pulled the company through the depression and the challenges of the s in  with teague as the manager he built the company into the states largest citrus holding and the worlds largest acreage the company also joined the southern california fruit exchange before pulling out a few years later and joining again in  the company also once set the record for deepest oil well in ventura county before abandoning the well in  the well like many o